08/08/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- On Friday (6 August), 279 new border police officers graduated from the OSCE-supported Idrizovo Police Academy in Macedonia.
They are the second generation of cadets from different ethnic backgrounds to have attended the training programme.
The officers will be assigned to work at crossings in the southern and eastern border areas.
So far, nearly 550 cadets have graduated from the academy;
their number is expected to increase by 1,000 by the end of 2005.
(Makfax, Vest - 07/08/04;
OSCE Web site - 06/08/04)
